The paper discusses a search technology for high-dimensional vector data, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and database (cs.DB) research. The use of graph-based indexes is also a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Additionally, the paper proposes new methods for adjusting the degrees of the graph, which is a problem commonly studied in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
